tool_description: Formula 1 data for the ultimate motorsport fanatic!
title: F1 Live Motorsport Data

api_list.name: Session
api_list.description: Provides session details for a given `session id` found in the Races endpoint. Contains information on drivers times, session weather, speed traps, and session status. Updated throughout each session.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://f1-live-motorsport-data.p.rapidapi.com/session/{session_id}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "f1-live-motorsport-data.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

drivers_array.comments: String - updated post session, may contain info on retirement pr penalities etc.
drivers_array.current_tyre: String - available in qualifying sessions and race only
drivers_array.did_not_start: Integer - 1 or 0; whether driver started race or not
drivers_array.disqualified: Integer - 1 or 0; whether driver was disqualified or not
drivers_array.gap: String - gap to driver in lead; leader will be blank
drivers_array.interval: String - gap to driver in front; race only
drivers_array.name: String
drivers_array.retired: Integer - 1 or 0; whether driver retired from race
drivers_array.stops: Integer - number of pits; only relevant to race, consider displaying current_lap value in non-race sessions
drivers_array.time: String - non-race sessions fastest lap; race last lap

details.finished_ts: String - Indicates when the chequered flag was waived. Blank OR ISO UTC Format Timestamp 2020-08-09T13:10:00+00:00
details.laps: Integer - Number of completed laps in session. In non-race sessions, this value is the highest number of laps completed by a driver in that session
details.status: String - Not Started, In Progress, Podium, Finished

flag_history_array.flag: String - NS=Not Started, G=Green, Y=Yellow, R=Red, C=Chequered
flag_history_array.session_timer: String - non-race sessions, countdown; race session elapsed time

general.session_name: String - Practice 1, Practice 2, Practice 3, Qualifying 1, Qualifying 2, Qualifying 3, Grid, Race, FastestLap

speed.note: Default is null; will be null for Grid and FastestLap files; sessions prior to 2020 season do not associated speed data

details.comments: Hamilton scored an additional point for setting the fastest lap of the race. The classification is subject to appeals lodged with the ICA. Magnussen received a 5-second time penalty for leaving the track and rejoining unsafely.
